    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Make global configuration possible for some options and easier for the other.\n\nSome of the idea of what its config fields:\n\n- `job = { threads: int, timeout: int }`. `job.threads` is the number of parallel threads to use (currently twice the number of CPU threads). `job.timeout` is a timeout for any async operation in milliseconds (currently 30000).\n\n- `add = { <the structure of opts in vim.pack.add()> }`. This allows setting default value of options in `vim.pack.add()` in a forward compatible way. Also see #34770. Counter-point is that the same can be achieved by writing custom wrapper around `vim.pack.add()`, but I think it is worth adding here.\n\n    NOTE: This assumes that there will be something like `opts.default_version` to allow to set it to `vim.version.range('*')` which would prefer latest tag release instead of default branch. If not, it might be part of `vim.pack.config()` directly.",
    "closed_at": null,
